$ PLS-00201: identifier 'DBMS_LOCK' must be declared

If the user who is trying to execute `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/lock/sleep` receives the error message *→ development/databases/Oracle/PL-SQL/errors-warnings/PLS-00201_identifier_must-be-declared[PLS-00201]: identifier 'DBMS_LOCK' must be declared*, this is likely because he wasn't granted EXECUTE on the
`→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/lock` package.
-
In this case, the user should try → development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/session/api/sleep[`dbms_session.sleep`]
